    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is the deck that bring me to the first place.  The fellowship might look weak, but it&#39;s far to be.  <br>
<br>
Always bid low.  Going first is&#39;nt important at all.  Most of the deck start the inn anyway, so you&#39;ll get sam quickly.  Against Nazgul player, I suggest starting lego+sam if they start pony.<br>
<br>
The stealth will make your opponent cause very little damage to this fellowship before site 5, so you can set the fellowship at 6 for the end.  Alway thror map for site 7 if you have it all, no matter the ton of ally opponent might have.<br>
<br>
The fellowship is just strong against all played culture.  It can just handle anything if played right and not taking stupid risk.<br>
<br>
The card drawing of the fellowship help for<br>
1)  Draw your companion, stealth and ally faster.  Since I almost start the fellowship with a 11 cards hand and the only thing I don&#39;t drop on table are the stealth, this leave my hand full of shadow for my unlucky opponent.  I&#39;ve not count the intimidated face I&#39;ve see just cause they sting my hand (Ask Alex about this).<br>
<br>
So that it, have fun trying it and making variant.  Anyway, there is now a lot of deck to try with TTT.<br>
